# Simple Blog Web App using Flask

This is a basic blog web application built using Flask, a Python web framework. The application allows users to view, create, and manage blog posts.

## Features

- View a list of recent blog posts on the home page.
- Click on a post title to view its content on a separate page.
- Create new blog posts by providing a title and content.

1.  Install the required dependencies:
    pip install Flask Flask-SQLAlchemy

2.  Create the database:
    python3
    from app import db
    db.create_all()
    exit()

3. Usage: 
     Start the development server:
        python app.py

    The app will be accessible at http://127.0.0.1:5000/.

    Visit the homepage to see the list of recent blog posts.

    Click on a post title to view its full content.

    To create a new post, click the "Create New Post" link on the homepage, provide a title and content, and submit the form.

